Japan to Provide Debt Relief Grant to Pakistan
ISLAMABAD , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The Japanese government will provide 75.211 million yen ( 650,000 U.S. dollars ) to Pakistan as grant assistance for the refinancing repayment obligations .
Official notes to this effect were exchanged here Monday between Minoru Kubota , the Japanese ambassador in Islamabad , and Zaheer Sajjad , secretary of the Economic Affairs Division , on behalf of their respective governments .
The grant will be used by the Pakistani government as a balance of payments support for purchasing commodities like electrical machinery , transport equipment , optical and medical instruments , scientific apparatus mutually agreed upon by the two governments .
